.SH "DRA-NOTIFY"
.IX Header "DRA-NOTIFY"
dra-notify \- Executes a script and sends out an email notification of the results
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
This documentation refers to dra-notify version 2.0.
.SH "USAGE"
.IX Header "USAGE"
\&\fBUsage: dra-notify [\-help] [script]\fR
.SH "REQUIRED ARGUMENTS"
.IX Header "REQUIRED ARGUMENTS"
A \fBscript\fR or executable file is required for dra-notify to run. Use the
path relative to \s-1DRA_HOME\s0
.PP
Examples:
.PP
To execute dra-run and have dra-notify send you the results:
.PP
\&\fBdra-notify bin/dra\-run\fR
.PP
To run the Auer Hall script:
.PP
\&\fBdra-notify \-name \*(L"Auer Hall\*(R" scripts/auerHall.sh\fR
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
\&\fB\-help\fR Displays brief synopsis of usage.
.PP
\&\fB\-name\fR Allows you to specify a name for the script in the subject line of
the email.  Otherwise, the path to the script will be used.
.PP
\&\fB\-email\fR Overrides the email setting in dra.conf.
.PP
\&\fB\-sender\fR Overrides the sender setting in dra.conf.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
dra-notify is a simple wrapper command that executes any script and 
emails the results.
.SH "DIAGNOSTICS"
.IX Header "DIAGNOSTICS"
dra-notify only reports the success or failure of the script it is calling.
.SH "CONFIGURATION AND ENVIRONMENT"
.IX Header "CONFIGURATION AND ENVIRONMENT"
A properly configured dra.conf and the \s-1DRA_HOME\s0 environment variable are required.
